title: For Sale:  Response to "RELOADS ARE ILLEGAL" post
postcontent: I believe you are misinformed. There are several large companies that sell remanufactured (reloaded) ammo across the country. Retailers like midway even carry it.  There is also no license required to sell ammunition. There is no such FFL for selling ammo. The only FFL one would need is a type 06 or type 07 if they wanted to reload ammunition AND sell it as a business FOR PROFIT. Also should mention it is extremely difficult to prove you loaded what you sold AND you made a profit. Selling a few here and there and trading does NOT require an FFL and you can only get an FFL (other than a C&R) if you are engaged in the business TO MAKE MONEY.   An individual would definitely assume risk/liability for the reloads. Your "friend" that supposedly went to jail must have been 1- reloading the ammo himself, 2- selling the ammo himself, and 3- doing so much business that he attracted the attention of the ATF (maybe by mailing it through the post office or selling it to people that can't legally buy it). BTW, I am a licensed manufacturer so I kind of know what the rules are since I have to follow them.

title: For Sale:  Colt Gold Cup Trophy 1911 SS .45 ACP 45 O5070X
postcontent: This is a brand new in box Colt Gold Cup Trophy 1911 semi-automatic pistol chambered for .45 ACP. The Colt Gold Cup is known as the finest shooting semi-automatic in the world, and is the standard for competitive guns. The first Colt Gold Cup pistol was introduced in the late 1950’s to give competitive shooters a gun to take directly from the dealer’s showcase to the firing line. This pistol features Brushed Stainless Steel frames and slides for excellent strength, and their solid construction makes reduces muzzle flip, making follow-up shots quicker and more accurate. A target post front sight and fully adjustable Bomar style rear sight provide the basis for pinpoint precision. The 5" National Match barrel extracts maximum energy and accuracy from the potent .45 ACP cartridge, and the included 7 and 8 round magazines permit rapid delivery. The wide, grooved, three hole aluminum trigger provides plenty of traction with minimal travel. The standard grip safety with beavertail and thumb safety improve safety and increase handling confidence. This pistol uses the series 80 firing system and boasts a lowered and flared ejection port for more reliable performance. Aggresively checkered polymer grips with a front wraparound provide and solid hold, even in rapid fire competitive or defensive shooting.

title: For Sale:  Concealed Weapons Permit Classes $75 Pensacola
postcontent:
Here is a list of my current class schedule and registration link for them. You can register now and pay on the day of class.                

Mar 15th Class 9am – 2pm – Registration link http://www.nrainstructors.org/SignupStudent.aspx?id=232697

Mar 30th Class 9am – 2pm – Registration link http://www.nrainstructors.org/SignupStudent.aspx?id=232699

Apr 12th Class 9am – 2pm – Registration link http://www.nrainstructors.org/SignupStudent.aspx?id=232702

Apr 27th Class 9am – 2pm – Registration link http://www.nrainstructors.org/SignupStudent.aspx?id=232703

The class is the NRA Basic Pistol / FL Concealed Weapons Permit class.  It covers safety, hands on classroom training, live fire training at the range, personal gun selection, cleaning/caring for a firearm and the laws/rules/procedures for the FL Concealed Weapons Permit. I also have a section of the class dedicated to personal defense with a firearm.  It is not necessary to own a firearm to attend the class as I have demo models.  If you own a firearm I recommend you bring it to class so you can train with it.  We typically spend 3 to 3 1/2 hours in the classroom and about an hour on the range. Once you complete the class you will receive a certificate that satisfies the requirements for the FL CWP.  You then fill out an application, have your fingerprints and picture taken and submit the application.  The cost of the actual permit is $70 and the fingerprint / back round check is $42.  The permit is good for 7 years.  I hold the public classes in the conference rooms at Homewood Suites by Pensacola Airport (or your location for a private class of 4 or more students).  The class is $75 per student and may be paid in cash, money order or local check.  

Please visit my Facebook Page "Pensacola Concealed Weapons Permit Classes" (https://www.facebook.com/ConcealedWeaponsPermitClasses) for more information and reviews.

Please call, text or email me with any questions. REDACTED  
Thanks
Wayne Briske
NRA Instructor #202302461

title: For Sale:  ATTENTION EVERYONE!!!
postcontent:
If an add says Arkansas, Arkansas, it's likely a scam!
If the price is too good to be true, it's likely a scam!
If they refuse to meet face to face or use paypal, it's likely a scam!
If the description in unnecessarily long and feels like it's copy and pasted from another site, it's likely a scam!

I know this is obvious to most of you but someone must still be falling for these weak a$$ scams or else these a$$hole$ wouldn't be posting 10 of them a day!

So if you recognize them as scams, report them and get them off!
If you're one of the idiots who send these people money, stop! Buy guns from your local gun store because you're obviously not smart enough to pick one out by yourself!
